  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rwanda: Help 82 kids study without Covid-19 risks.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">When schools reopened in Rwanda after a whole year due to COVID-19 the challenge has been accommodating children. Despite the construction of additional classrooms, still classrooms were over-crowded. This is how SPES NOVA Junior Academy was created to help address the issue. Since then, the school embarked on a long process of finding enough classrooms, school equipment and materials, teachers for 82 kids. Unfortunately, the school still needs basic facilities such as water and toilets.</narrative>
  </description>
